---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const src = 'https://renalcarematters.com/guides/hemodialysis-transfer-guide.html';
---
<BaseLayout title="Transferring your care" description="How to change dialysis centers or nephrologists safely — the right documents, the right process, and no missed sessions.">
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px">
      <a href="/kidney-health" style="font-weight:700;text-decoration:none">← Kidney Health Hub</a>
      <h1 style="margin-top:14px">Transferring your care</h1>
      <p class="lead">You have every right to change centers — here's how to do it safely, without missing a session.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:.9rem">Adapted with permission from <a href={src}>renalcarematters.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>It's your right</h2>
      <p>You are allowed to change dialysis centers, change nephrologists, seek a second opinion, and get
      copies of your records. Transferring — because of a move, finances, a referral, or personal choice —
      is completely normal.</p>

      <h2>Just don't stop abruptly</h2>
      <p>The risk isn't transferring — it's transferring <em>abruptly</em>, without informing your current
      team or confirming your new center. A single missed session can cause severe fluid overload and
      dangerously high potassium within <strong>24–72 hours</strong>. The safe transfer is
      <strong>planned, documented, and continuous</strong>.</p>

      <h2>The right way to do it</h2>
      <ul style="line-height:1.9">
        <li>Tell your current team and ask for a proper endorsement.</li>
        <li>Request copies of your records, recent labs, and your dialysis prescription.</li>
        <li>Confirm your new center can accept you and has a slot — <strong>before</strong> your next session is due.</li>
        <li>Bring your PhilHealth Member Data Record (MDR) and medicine list.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="notice"><strong>We make transfers easy.</strong> Bring your latest dialysis records and
      we'll take care of continuity so there's no gap in your treatment.</div>

      <p style="margin-top:20px"><a href="/new-patients#request" class="btn btn--primary">Transfer to St. John Biocare</a></p>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:22px;font-size:.9rem">Adapted with permission from
        <a href={src}>renalcarematters.com</a>. Medically reviewed by a nephrologist. Educational only;
        not a substitute for consultation.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
